comment: Lemma for ~ binomcxp . By the power and chain rules, calculate the derivative of ` ( ( 1 + b ) ^c -u C ) ` , with respect to ` b ` in the disk of convergence ` D ` . We later multiply the derivative in the later ~ binomcxplemdvsum by this derivative to show that ` ( ( 1 + b ) ^c C ) ` (with a non-negated ` C ` ) and the later sum, since both at ` b = 0 ` equal one, are the same. (Contributed by Steve Rodriguez, 22-Apr-2020.)
